.TH DISCIMAGECREATOR 1 "2026-06-15" "DiscImageCreator suite" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
discimagecreator \- low-level optical disc dumper
.br
eccedc, dvdauth, unscrambler \- DiscImageCreator suite helper tools
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B discimagecreator
.I command
.RI [ options ...]
.PP
.B eccedc
.I command
.RI [ options ...]
.PP
.B dvdauth
.I command
.RI [ options ...]
.PP
.B unscrambler
.I command
.RI [ options ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B discimagecreator
is a command-line tool for byte-perfect dumping of optical discs (CD,
GD, DVD, HD-DVD, BD, GameCube, Wii, XBOX, XBOX 360) and various disk
types (Floppy, MO, USB). It is one of the dumpers supported by the
Redump preservation project for production-grade media submissions.
.PP
This package bundles four binaries from the same upstream author:
.TP
.B discimagecreator
The main dumper. Real binary
.B DiscImageCreator.out
in libexec (upstream-original filename). Aliases in PATH:
.B discimagecreator
(canonical lowercase),
.B dic
(short form), and
.B DiscImageCreator.out
itself (kept in PATH for MPF default-config compatibility).
.TP
.B eccedc
Validates or repairs sector ECC/EDC on the 2048-byte user-data area of
CDs. Used post-dump to confirm sector integrity. The real binary
.B EccEdc.out
sits in the package's libexec directory and is spawned automatically
by
.B discimagecreator
when needed; the
.B eccedc
alias exists for direct user invocation.
.TP
.B dvdauth
Performs CSS, CPPM, or CPRM authentication for DVD reading on supported
drives. Real binary
.B DVDAuth.out
in libexec.
.TP
.B unscrambler
Brute-forces unscrambling for non-standard scrambled DVDs (typically
GameCube/Wii optical disks). Real binary
.B unscrambler.out
in libexec.
.SH DRIVE ACCESS
.B discimagecreator
and
.B dvdauth
ship with the
.B cap_sys_rawio
file capability set, so they can issue SCSI vendor commands (e.g.\&
Plextor read method D8, Kreon XGD passthrough) without root.
.PP
The invoking user must additionally have access to
.IR /dev/sr* :
membership in the
.B cdrom
group, or an active uaccess seat assignment, is sufficient on Fedora.
.SH DATA FILES
Drive-offset tables and protection databases ship in
.IR /usr/share/discimagecreator/ :
.IP \(bu 2
.I default.dat
\(em main database.
.IP \(bu 2
.I driveOffset.txt
\(em drive read offset table.
.IP \(bu 2
.I C2ErrorProtect.txt
\(em C2-error-based protection signatures.
.IP \(bu 2
.I ReadErrorProtect.txt
\(em read-error-based protection signatures.
.IP \(bu 2
"DVDRawBruteforce - Drive Sheet - Sheet1.tsv"
\(em raw-DVD brute-force drive sheet.
.PP
The binary's data-directory probe path is patched at build time from
upstream's
.I /usr/share/DiscImageCreator/
to lowercase
.IR /usr/share/discimagecreator/ ;
no environment variable, working-directory tweak, or configuration file
is needed.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/libexec/discimagecreator/
Real binaries (main + three helpers). Not intended for direct PATH
invocation; use the
.IR /usr/bin/
aliases instead.
.TP
.I /usr/share/discimagecreator/
Bundled data files (see DATA FILES above).
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/discimagecreator/
Upstream changelog, tested-drive list, firmware notes, known issues,
specs and protocol references (full
.I Release_ANSI/Doc/
tree).
